Model_Package_Description_Profile:ModelP.descriptionText:
New York Data Exchange (NYDEx) Information Exchange Package & Documentation.
This document provides additional documentation necessary to understand the contents of the New York Data Exchange (NYDEx) Information Exchange Package Documentation (IEPD). This IEPD, created by a team at New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services (herein referred to as DCJS), will provide authorized New York State Law Enforcement agencies with the ability to exchange Incident data in XML format.
The New York Data Exchange (NYDEx) IEPD is based on version 2 of the National Information Exchange Model1 (NIEM).
By no means should you consider this document to be a complete or formal design document. All artifacts included in the IEPD work in conjunction to specify content of the New York State Incident report.
Model_Package_Description_Profile:ModelP.ASName: New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services
Model_Package_Description_Profile:ModelP.PurposeText:
The purpose of the New York Data Exchange (NYDEx) IEPD is to specify the XML content model for the exchange of Incident data created and by New York State Law Enforcement agencies.
This IEPD and its exchange model define the schema for the New York State Incident Report content.
Model_Package_Description_Profile:ModelP.ExchangePatternText:
Though XML schema can accommodate certain business rules it is unable to capture all necessary rules. This section includes business rules that you must consider when generating an XML instance that conforms to this IEPD.
  • The root element for NYDEx is
  • ORI must be completed with the nine-character identifier (ORI) assigned by the FBI CJIS staff to the organization where the information originated.
  • Agency Contact must be provided, and each must include at least First Name, Last Name, and Telephone Number.
  • Activity report dates must be same or postdate Activity begin dates.
  • End dates/times must be later than start dates/times.
  • An Incident Number can be no more than 50 characters in length, must be unique to the incident, and must be provided, if Activity Incident is provided.
  • An Incident Exceptional Clearance Date must not predate Incident date.
  • An Offense Code must be provided, if Activity Offense is provided
  • At least one entity with an Officer role must be provided if Arrest activity is provided.
  • No more than one Arrest Location may be provided per Arrest Report.
  • No more than one Arrestee may be provided per Arrest Report
  • An Arrest date must not predate Incident date.
  • An Arrest Narrative Account Description date cannot predate the Incident Begin Date, Incident Report Date, or Arrest Date.
  • A Service Call date must be the same as or predate Arrest date, Incident Report date, and Missing Person Declaration or Found dates.
  • Person relationships should make sense given the characteristics of the related people (e.g., if Person A is the parent of Person B, then if their ages are known, Person B should be younger than Person A).
  • Person SSN can be either 9 digits absent any dashes, spaces, or special characters of the form NNNNNNNNN, or 11 characters of the form NNN-NN-NNNN where 'N' is one of the digits 0 through 9. No partials or other formats are accepted.
  • Person FBI Number, Person Driver License Number, Person State ID, Person Passport ID, Person US Marshal Service Fugitive ID, Person Registered Offender Number, Person Identification Number may not include any dashes, spaces, or special characters. No partials or other formats are accepted.
  • If a Person Driver License Number, Person State ID, Person Registered Offender Number, or Person Identification Number is supplied, then either the Issuing Authority Code or Issuing Authority Text field must be provided for each number.
  • The unit of measurement must be supplied for any measurement values, whether range or exact value.
  • A VIN Number cannot be identical to the Owner Applied ID.
  • A Boat Hull Serial Number cannot be identical to the Boat Owner Applied ID.
  • If Location County is provided, then Location State must also be provided.
